{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"alias":"soar-quill-flare","description":"## Summary\nExecute the SAFE ROLLOUT of epic 3006-e198 after the foundation (amiss-bun-wince / baf7) and the four drift-class heals land: baseline dual-write shadow, shadow consumer with divergence alerting, the prev_snapshot->baseline consumer swap, live circuit-breaker wiring, and the capped live heal of the 7 known drift instances. Approved remediations 1+2 from the 2026-07-03 derisk evaluation live here. Deployment context: .github/workflows/reconcile-bridge.yml runs `rebar reconcile --mode live` every 20 min from main; its workflow_dispatch `mode` input is the ROLLBACK BRAKE (pin to dry-run) at every step below.\n\n## Phase 1 — baseline dual-write shadow (approved remediation 2)\n- In the live pass (reconcile.py, after the existing baseline-advance at pass end), when config `reconciler.baseline_dual_write=true`: call `BindingStore.set_baseline` for every bound key from the pass's curr snapshot, WITHOUT changing any consumer (outbound_fields still reads prev_snapshot).\n- Each pass logs `SyncLogger.log(\"baseline_shadow_check\", equal=N, divergent=M, keys=[...])` comparing the stored baseline vs the prev_snapshot values for the 5 mirrored fields; any M>0 raises a bridge_alert.\n- GATE: >= 10 consecutive clean passes (M==0) recorded before Phase 3. Passes are ~20 min apart, so this is ~3.5 hours of wall clock minimum.\n\n## Phase 2 — shadow consumer + divergence alert (approved remediation 1 wiring)\n- Every pass, in EVERY mode, emit the foundation's decision_census record (counts, acting_pct, breaker verdict) via sync_logger.\n- Run the classifier in REPORT mode against the same pass artifacts and log any divergence between its acting set and the acting mutations the legacy path planned; divergence -> bridge_alert. (This is the level-triggered path auditing the edge-triggered path before it replaces it.)\n\n## Phase 3 — consumer swap (the ONE high-risk seam; do this last and alone)\n- Re-point `outbound_fields._local_matches_prev` (and its caller in outbound_differ) from prev_snapshot values to `BindingStore.get_baseline`; PRESERVE: absent-baseline -> local-wins degrade; corrupt-store fail-closed pass abort; direction arbitration semantics byte-for-byte (ADR 0026 #1-#3).\n- prev_snapshot is NOT deleted in this ticket: L3 single-pass suppression still computes outbound+inbound against the same snapshot (ADR 0029 #3). Removing prev_snapshot entirely is a follow-up only after N clean passes.\n- RED-first test: the direction-preservation property must run against the SWAPPED consumer (a Jira-side edit with local==baseline is mirrored inbound, never reverted).\n\n## Phase 4 — live heal under caps\n- Wire check_blast_radius into the apply path: a pass whose acting decisions exceed `reconciler.max_acting_fraction` (default 0.10) aborts with a bridge_alert BEFORE any mutation.\n- workflow_dispatch the reconciler at mode=bootstrap-strict (MODE_CAPS=10) to heal the 7 known instances (5x archived->Done, 1x GC REB-530 after grace, 1x adopt REB-532); verify the NEXT pass's census reports 0 acting decisions (fixed point reached on live data); then return to live.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Dual-write shadow behind `reconciler.baseline_dual_write` with per-pass baseline_shadow_check logging + alert on divergence; >= 10 consecutive clean live passes recorded (cite pass ids in a closing comment).\n- [ ] decision_census emitted every pass in every mode; classifier-vs-legacy divergence logged + alerting in shadow.\n- [ ] Consumer swap merged with the direction-preservation property test running against the swapped consumer; corrupt-baseline fail-closed abort preserved; prev_snapshot retained for L3.\n- [ ] Circuit breaker enforced in the apply path (abort BEFORE first mutation, alert emitted); config default 0.10.\n- [ ] The 7 known drift instances healed under bootstrap-strict caps; next-pass census = 0 acting decisions; evidence (census log excerpts) attached to this ticket.\n- [ ] Rollback procedure (pin workflow mode input to dry-run) documented in docs/jira-sync-setup.md.","id":"7d23-106a-d7cc-42fb","parent_id":"3006-e198-13db-4e1f","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Convergence rollout: dual-write shadow, census/divergence alerting, prev_snapshot->baseline consumer swap, breaker wiring, capped live heal"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783105707261586001,"uuid":"93d096c0-94fc-4435-929e-06df9574cce2"}